
[1]rhubarb

   RHU'BARB, n.

   A plant of the genus Rheum, of several species; as the rhapontic, or
   common rhubarb; the palmated, or true Chinese rhubarb; the compact or
   Tartarian; the undulated or wave-leafed Chinese rhubarb; and the rubes,
   or currant rhubarb of mount Libanus. The root is medicinal and much
   used as a moderate cathartic.
